 in an attempt to manipulate the relationship between spectator and performance, this book pioneers a shift in our understanding of audience as both theoretical concept and historical phenomenon.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aItalian dramay18th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aItalian dramayTo 1700xHistory and criticism. 0aSpectatorszItalyxHistoryy17th century. 0aSpectatorszItalyxHistoryy18th century. 0aTheater audienceszItalyxHistoryy17th century. 0aTheater audienceszItalyxHistoryy18th century. 0aTheater audienceszItalyxPsychologyxHistoryy17th century. 0aTheater audienceszItalyxPsychologyxHistoryy18th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Italian.2bisacsh  aart.  aaudience.  adrama.  adramaturgy.  ahistory of the theatre.  aitalian history.  aitalian literature.  aitalian theatre.  aliterature.  aperformance studies.  apublic sphere.  aspectators.  atheatre studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishz978311061036908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2019z9783110606348oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065206240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753208640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487532086423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487532086.jpg  a978-3-11-061036-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  